	   <tr><td colspan=2>To all the non-pet owning people who wondered why the DS is useful.&nbsp;&nbsp;As a mage I too occasionally enter the fray.  The occasion is if my pet is low on health and I dont want him to die.  I will go in and take a few hits to ensure my pet doesn't die, and then have the mob agro on me after its dead and kill me cause I can't get a spell off.  So fighting occasionally is important. <br><br>And I know the next question is why not nuke it and kill the mob or jsut summon another pet right?  Well for myself, I have a set amount of mana I know I can use for that mob and still have enough for the next spawn.  So if I'm approaching the alotted mana for the mob I'll save it to finish it off or for the next spawn.<br><br><br>That is also where a DS comis in handy cause I know I'm gonna get spanked and at least I'll be able to do SOME damage back.<br><br>So what haave we learned today?  Mana Conservation Good.<br><br>Inestyne, Mage Extrordinaire<br>Tarew Marr<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
