	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Mar 15th 2:42 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[4.16]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Proccing a damage shield is no different than proccing a self-buff (like the Screaming Mace does) -- while in combat using this staff, there is a chance based off of your dex that it will proc, casting a damage shield on you.&nbsp;&nbsp;The two-handed practice sword, in play since Kunark, has a similar effect.<br><br>That said, this effect doesn't seem so useful, given that the staff is wieldable only by casters -- if a caster is both (a) in battle and swinging this staff instead of casting/medding and (b) the target of the mob's aggression instead of the group tanks, then something is going seriously wrong.<br><br>That said, the stats/mana/saves are pretty nice. :)  I'm just not sure the proc is anything but a point of curiosity.<br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
